WEBVTT

00:06.048 --> 00:07.340
<i>Previously on</i> Reacher...

00:07.341 --> 00:08.925
[Reacher] <i>Lieutenant Colonel
Francis Xavier Quinn.</i>

00:08.926 --> 00:10.301
[Duffy] <i>You want to find him?</i>

00:10.302 --> 00:11.970
- [Reacher] <i>Yeah.</i>
- [Duffy] <i>So maybe
we can help each other out.</i>

00:11.971 --> 00:14.472
You're gonna get in with Beck
by saving his son

00:14.473 --> 00:16.933
<i>- from getting kidnapped again.</i>
- [Reacher] <i>Undercover informant?</i>

00:16.934 --> 00:18.768
The last one you had went missing.

00:18.769 --> 00:20.520
[Duffy] <i>So what can I do for you?</i>

00:20.521 --> 00:23.481
<i>[Reacher] After the fake grenade blasts
and a gunfight,</i>

00:23.482 --> 00:25.358
<i>- Richard won't come with me easily.</i>
- [Villanueva] <i>So what do we do?</i>

00:25.359 --> 00:28.027
We take the option of going to the police
completely off the table.

00:28.028 --> 00:29.988
- [grunts]
- You shot a cop!

00:29.989 --> 00:32.532
<i>- My dad's rich. He can help you.</i>
- Mr. Reacher.

00:32.533 --> 00:35.410
I'm Zachary Beck.
I need to see if you can follow orders.

00:35.411 --> 00:37.245
I'm in.

00:37.246 --> 00:39.539
<i>- How's the bodyguard?</i>
- He's not saying shit.

00:39.540 --> 00:40.832
[Reacher] <i>Well, I might have
a lead on the girl.</i>

00:40.833 --> 00:43.001
<i>Could've been taken into the carriage
house where there's a hidden cellar.</i>

00:43.002 --> 00:45.129
- [Duffy] <i>Is Teresa there?</i>
- No.

00:46.422 --> 00:47.465
But she was.

00:49.341 --> 00:51.343
[tense music playing]

00:56.390 --> 00:57.932
[Duffy over phone] <i>I knew
Teresa was there.</i>

00:57.933 --> 00:59.350
<i>Do you see anything else?</i>

00:59.351 --> 01:01.186
Half-eaten plate of food.

01:01.187 --> 01:04.272
Same one I saw Beck's head of security
take out of the house a few hours ago.

01:04.273 --> 01:06.691
- So Teresa was moved tonight.
<i>- We just missed her.</i>

01:06.692 --> 01:08.902
<i>- She could be somewhere in the house.</i>
- No.

01:08.903 --> 01:10.695
With my arrival
and Richard being home now,

01:10.696 --> 01:12.322
there's too much activity on the grounds.

01:12.323 --> 01:14.532
Too many uncertainties.

01:14.533 --> 01:16.409
They took her off the property.

01:16.410 --> 01:17.911
Security cameras?

01:17.912 --> 01:19.120
From what I saw at the gatehouse,

01:19.121 --> 01:20.705
eight cameras facing
the only road in or out.

01:20.706 --> 01:22.332
Can you get a look at the footage?

01:22.333 --> 01:23.875
<i>The film wouldn't show anything.</i>

01:23.876 --> 01:25.835
Whoever took Teresa
would have her in the trunk.

01:25.836 --> 01:27.921
No way to know what car
she left in or where they took her

01:27.922 --> 01:29.798
once she was out of sight of the cameras.

01:29.799 --> 01:31.299
They could be taking her
somewhere to kill her.

01:31.300 --> 01:32.509
<i>There's no blood in here.</i>

01:32.510 --> 01:33.927
No sign of any struggle.

01:33.928 --> 01:36.262
There is a cot, a blanket, a space heater.

01:36.263 --> 01:39.057
<i>- They fed her.</i>
- [sighs] Thank God.

01:39.058 --> 01:41.684
It's not good news.

01:41.685 --> 01:45.230
If the people who have her
are involved with a guy like Quinn,

01:45.231 --> 01:48.942
they're not keeping her alive and healthy
for a good reason.

01:48.943 --> 01:51.402
- Fuck.
<i>- We'll find her again.</i>

01:51.403 --> 01:54.030
I got to get back to my room
before the rest of the house wakes up.

01:54.031 --> 01:55.324
Okay.

01:56.325 --> 01:58.327
[crickets chirping]

02:05.709 --> 02:07.711
[tense music playing]

02:20.432 --> 02:22.433
[Duke] What took you so long?

02:22.434 --> 02:24.854
[speaking indistinctly]

02:32.361 --> 02:34.363
[Cooper sighing]

02:37.700 --> 02:40.493
Oh, shit, man.
I-I can't sleep in this thing.

02:40.494 --> 02:42.120
It's fucking uncomfortable.

02:42.121 --> 02:44.873
- You see me snoring?
- Oh. Come on, man.

02:44.874 --> 02:46.625
I got to some sleep at some point.

02:49.545 --> 02:51.547
You got the score of the Sox game?

02:52.590 --> 02:55.049
Orioles: five, Red Sox: three.

02:55.050 --> 02:57.051
Goddamn it.

02:57.052 --> 02:58.469
[Eliot] Hey, what's up, boss?

02:58.470 --> 02:59.888
[Duffy] What's Beck doing with Teresa?

02:59.889 --> 03:00.972
- Oh, fuck.
- [Eliot] Hey!

03:00.973 --> 03:02.974
- You don't want to do this.
- Back off! Why are they keeping her?

03:02.975 --> 03:04.767
- I don't know anything about any Teresa.
- [Duffy] Bullshit.

03:04.768 --> 03:06.019
I know she was there.

03:06.020 --> 03:07.478
I told you, I'm just a bodyguard.

03:07.479 --> 03:09.480
I ran your jacket, John Cooper.

03:09.481 --> 03:11.149
- Fuck. Whatever.
- A year for domestic abuse.

03:11.150 --> 03:12.901
Four years, aggravated assault.

03:12.902 --> 03:14.819
Not someone I'd hire to babysit.

03:14.820 --> 03:16.070
[spits] Fuck you.

03:16.071 --> 03:17.947
- Fuck.
- What the hell?

03:17.948 --> 03:19.991
[overlapping shouting]

03:19.992 --> 03:21.868
- Come on!
- [shouting]

03:21.869 --> 03:23.578
- [Villanueva] Go cool down!
- They have Teresa!

03:23.579 --> 03:25.580
- Go cool down.
- They're keeping her prisoner.

03:25.581 --> 03:27.916
I said step outside and cool down, kid.

03:27.917 --> 03:29.209
Now.

03:30.628 --> 03:31.962
[Cooper] Yeah.

03:33.047 --> 03:34.506
Fuck, man.

03:36.926 --> 03:39.302
Twelve bucks of coffee, wasted.

03:39.303 --> 03:41.347
How about you keep a leash on that bitch?

03:44.099 --> 03:47.770
Call her that again, and I'll leave her
alone with you for an hour.

03:51.398 --> 03:53.525
[laughs softly] Thought so.

03:59.657 --> 04:01.574
[Duffy] If that piece of shit
knows anything--

04:01.575 --> 04:03.910
That piece of shit
is being illegally detained.

04:03.911 --> 04:07.413
- No, we can claim that we have--
- We can claim my ass is a ham steak,

04:07.414 --> 04:09.916
but at the end of day,
it's just full of shit.

04:09.917 --> 04:12.335
Look, if we can't pin
any of Beck's dirt on him,

04:12.336 --> 04:15.755
which is a distinct possibility,
eventually, we got to set him free,

04:15.756 --> 04:18.341
and there's gonna be nothing
to stop him from singing about all this.

04:18.342 --> 04:20.426
Eh, he won't talk, he's a fucking skell.

04:20.427 --> 04:22.053
He'll just be happy to be gone.

04:22.054 --> 04:25.890
Maybe. But if you keep beating his ass,
he might carry a beef.

04:25.891 --> 04:27.725
Then who knows what he does.

04:27.726 --> 04:29.310
So keep it cool, Susie Q.

04:29.311 --> 04:31.896
Seriously, Duffy.
This-this is already fucked enough.

04:31.897 --> 04:34.315
I don't want to hear shit
from you, Magellan.

04:34.316 --> 04:37.026
Look, Villy, walk away.

04:37.027 --> 04:38.653
I don't want you going down with us.

04:38.654 --> 04:40.321
Not on a favor I pulled you in on.

04:40.322 --> 04:42.365
Not on something
you had nothing to do with.

04:42.366 --> 04:44.617
Ain't bailing on you now, Irish.

04:44.618 --> 04:46.829
Just keep the RPMs down.

04:50.791 --> 04:52.418
Copy that.

04:55.212 --> 04:59.173
You, get inside and watch the perp.

04:59.174 --> 05:01.260
Do something useful.

05:08.767 --> 05:11.102
Magellan, huh?

05:11.103 --> 05:13.689
'Cause he couldn't read the map?

05:15.691 --> 05:17.734
Sometimes I call him "Ponce de Moron."

05:17.735 --> 05:20.236
[chuckles]

05:20.237 --> 05:22.321
Don't go too hard on him.

05:22.322 --> 05:24.490
He's still part of your team.

05:24.491 --> 05:26.617
Some team. [scoffs]

05:26.618 --> 05:31.414
A rookie, an old fart
and a gigantic vagrant we barely know.

05:31.415 --> 05:33.458
And who are you in all of this?

05:33.459 --> 05:35.961
The idiot who put it all together.

05:38.422 --> 05:39.923
[groans]

05:41.759 --> 05:43.634
- [Duke] What do you mean
you're not sure if it's there?
- [Angel] Well, I-I wasn't there.

05:43.635 --> 05:46.137
- Can your guy help me?
- The big guy inside?

05:46.138 --> 05:47.930
[Angel] Yeah, can he come with me?
He was at the kidnapping.

05:47.931 --> 05:49.599
[Duke] Come on, I'll get him.

05:49.600 --> 05:51.560
[Angel] I just want to make sure,
you know?

05:54.438 --> 05:56.230
[Duke] Anything else you want to tell me?

05:56.231 --> 05:58.317
[speaking indistinctly]

05:59.818 --> 06:01.820
[suspenseful music playing]

06:16.001 --> 06:17.919
Wait here.

06:17.920 --> 06:20.338
Can I go down to the kitchen
and grab a drink?

06:20.339 --> 06:22.091
I don't give a shit.

06:28.180 --> 06:29.598
[grunts]

06:35.979 --> 06:37.981
[grunting]

06:39.274 --> 06:41.276
[panting]

06:53.038 --> 06:55.833
[grunting]

06:58.168 --> 07:00.128
[exciting music playing]

07:00.129 --> 07:01.421
[keys jingle]

07:16.061 --> 07:17.855
♪ ♪

07:28.198 --> 07:30.325
[toilet flushes]

07:35.497 --> 07:37.039
Flattered, but no, thanks.

07:37.040 --> 07:39.167
Get dressed. There's a job for you.

07:39.168 --> 07:40.710
At 3:47?

07:40.711 --> 07:42.628
We found the pickup the kidnappers used.

07:42.629 --> 07:45.965
Cops took it to some state evidence lot
90 miles south of here.

07:45.966 --> 07:47.592
There's a guy downstairs. Angel Doll.

07:47.593 --> 07:51.179
He'll take you to I.D. the truck so
we figure out who tried to kidnap Richard.

07:51.180 --> 07:53.055
Give me five minutes to get dressed.

07:53.056 --> 07:54.766
You got two.

07:57.561 --> 07:58.978
[door closes]

07:58.979 --> 08:00.980
[panting]

08:00.981 --> 08:03.066
[water running]

08:06.069 --> 08:07.820
[line ringing]

08:07.821 --> 08:10.198
- [Duffy over phone] <i>Reacher?</i>
- I've got my first job.

08:10.199 --> 08:12.909
One of Beck's guys is taking me
to I.D. the Toyota pickup.

08:12.910 --> 08:16.579
We made sure all the vehicles involved
were sent to a state police impound lot.

08:16.580 --> 08:18.080
What the hell's their plan for getting in?

08:18.081 --> 08:21.209
Don't know.
I doubt they're gonna just ask nicely.

08:21.210 --> 08:22.418
Look, I know you said the vehicles

08:22.419 --> 08:24.003
<i>- won't come back to us, but--</i>
- They won't.

08:24.004 --> 08:26.505
They're all confiscated
as government contraband.

08:26.506 --> 08:28.633
If they run any plates,
nothing points back to you.

08:28.634 --> 08:31.469
Did you say all the vehicles
went to the same lot?

08:31.470 --> 08:34.180
- Yeah. Why?
<i>- The bodyguard's Audi will be there, too.</i>

08:34.181 --> 08:36.015
Beck thinks a real grenade
went off inside.

08:36.016 --> 08:38.809
The interior should be covered
with blood and brain matter.

08:38.810 --> 08:41.562
They see a pristine car,
the whole kidnapping story falls apart.

08:41.563 --> 08:43.397
Fuck. Okay.

08:43.398 --> 08:46.192
I'm gonna head out there and get
the Audi off the lot before you show up,

08:46.193 --> 08:47.485
but you got to buy me time.

08:47.486 --> 08:49.111
I'll do what I can,
but you better move your ass.

08:49.112 --> 08:50.321
We're leaving now.

08:50.322 --> 08:52.407
[thunder crashes]

09:09.007 --> 09:11.551
So, you were a cop in the Army, huh?

09:13.220 --> 09:16.472
Beck had me run your prints.

09:16.473 --> 09:19.308
What kind of connections you have that you
can get your prints processed that fast?

09:19.309 --> 09:21.269
[laughs] Shit, man.

09:21.270 --> 09:25.690
I got more hookups
than Central Maine Power Company.

09:25.691 --> 09:27.775
I was in the Army too, you know?

09:27.776 --> 09:30.111
Until I got thrown out for some bullshit.

09:30.112 --> 09:32.113
But fuck them, right?

09:32.114 --> 09:34.658
I make more money now
than I ever would have being a grunt.

09:35.701 --> 09:37.535
Duke called you "Angel Doll."

09:37.536 --> 09:38.744
Is that really your name?

09:38.745 --> 09:40.496
Ángel Dole.

09:40.497 --> 09:43.165
That other shit is just a nickname,

09:43.166 --> 09:46.294
'cause my grandma
used to call me her "angel doll"

09:46.295 --> 09:50.548
after I won the Most Beautiful Baby
contest at the county fair.

09:50.549 --> 09:52.091
It stuck, you know?

09:52.092 --> 09:54.343
You won?

09:54.344 --> 09:56.096
Fuck you, man.

09:59.933 --> 10:02.852
I thought Duke was gonna stick me
with that <i>pendejo</i> Paulie.

10:02.853 --> 10:04.937
Always got to play alpha bitch.

10:04.938 --> 10:06.564
But this is my shit today, man.

10:06.565 --> 10:09.817
Once we get back,
I'm gonna call my ex's Aunt Ginny--

10:09.818 --> 10:12.945
she works at the DMV--
she'll run the plates for me.

10:12.946 --> 10:15.364
Why would your ex's aunt help you?

10:15.365 --> 10:19.035
She still loves the shit out of me because
we always watched the <i>Wheel</i> together.

10:19.036 --> 10:20.786
Told you, bro.

10:20.787 --> 10:22.955
More hookups than the power company.

10:22.956 --> 10:25.374
Finding out who went after that kid,

10:25.375 --> 10:27.501
this is the kind of shit
that gets you bumped up, too.

10:27.502 --> 10:31.088
Even Duke used to do grunt work
at the warehouse.

10:31.089 --> 10:32.757
Look at him now, he's number two,

10:32.758 --> 10:35.217
living in that big mansion.

10:35.218 --> 10:36.719
So, Beck promotes from within?

10:36.720 --> 10:39.889
Who gives a fuck what Zachary Beck thinks?

10:39.890 --> 10:41.975
[dramatic music playing]

10:43.143 --> 10:45.186
Who exactly do we work for?

10:45.187 --> 10:46.395
[laughs]

10:46.396 --> 10:48.606
Got a lot to learn, big fella.

10:48.607 --> 10:50.192
Got a lot to learn.

10:53.111 --> 10:54.446
[door opens]

10:55.572 --> 10:57.031
You in charge?

10:57.032 --> 10:58.991
[officer] Uh, only one here,
so I better be.

10:58.992 --> 11:01.744
Agents Duffy and Villanueva, DEA.

11:01.745 --> 11:03.954
Several vehicles
were brought in here last night,

11:03.955 --> 11:06.165
and we need access to one of them.
Evidence sweep.

11:06.166 --> 11:08.667
Uh, yeah, sure.

11:08.668 --> 11:10.378
- Thanks. Just need a few minutes.
- [door buzzes]

11:10.379 --> 11:12.381
She's got it. I'll wait outside.

11:16.551 --> 11:18.553
[sighs]

11:19.930 --> 11:21.932
[tense music playing]

11:43.578 --> 11:44.788
[sighs]

11:51.169 --> 11:52.962
- [phone beeps]
- [line ringing]

11:52.963 --> 11:54.713
How's it looking?

11:54.714 --> 11:57.425
Like it's gonna take longer
than we thought.

11:57.426 --> 11:59.802
The Audi's pinned in.
I got to move a wreck to get it out.

11:59.803 --> 12:02.388
Hopefully Reacher's
figured out a way to stall.

12:02.389 --> 12:04.683
- [♪ Rick Coyne: "Had You So Long"]
- <i>♪ I know you too damn well ♪</i>

12:06.685 --> 12:08.562
<i>♪ To let it go ♪</i>

12:09.980 --> 12:12.649
<i>♪ I see your troubled mind ♪</i>

12:13.900 --> 12:16.069
<i>♪ Behind your lying eyes ♪</i>

12:19.072 --> 12:21.031
<i>♪ Don't tell me that ♪</i>

12:21.032 --> 12:23.785
- <i>♪ You're still in love with me...</i>
- [entry bell dings]

12:26.830 --> 12:28.414
The fuck you doing, man?

12:28.415 --> 12:29.915
We got to go.

12:29.916 --> 12:31.375
Just getting a coffee.

12:31.376 --> 12:33.919
Coffee? So, you just made me stop

12:33.920 --> 12:37.131
because you said
you had to "piss like a racehorse,"

12:37.132 --> 12:38.758
and now you're just getting
a large coffee?

12:40.010 --> 12:41.886
I was thirsty.

12:41.887 --> 12:43.846
Wha-- did you get me one?

12:43.847 --> 12:45.055
No.

12:45.056 --> 12:46.141
[entry bell dings]

12:50.061 --> 12:52.730
[tense music playing]

12:52.731 --> 12:54.482
[exhales]

12:54.483 --> 12:56.943
[straining]

12:58.445 --> 12:59.528
[Villanueva] <i>What's happening?</i>

12:59.529 --> 13:01.280
[grunts]

13:01.281 --> 13:02.364
Nothing.

13:02.365 --> 13:04.200
The whole front end's blown out.

13:04.201 --> 13:05.826
I'll come out to help you.

13:05.827 --> 13:08.162
No, no. I need you where you are
so I know when Reacher gets here.

13:08.163 --> 13:09.705
<i>You can't move it on your own.</i>

13:09.706 --> 13:13.793
And you can't lift a paint can
without your hernia belt, so stay put.

13:18.507 --> 13:21.592
Once we get there,
how do we get the cops to let us in?

13:21.593 --> 13:26.096
[chuckles] I got 500 bucks
for whoever is working that desk.

13:26.097 --> 13:27.932
Shitty night shift assignment,

13:27.933 --> 13:29.558
got to be some rookie,

13:29.559 --> 13:32.062
fresh out of the academy,
bottom of his class.

13:33.104 --> 13:35.481
People like that
don't turn down half a band.

13:35.482 --> 13:36.815
Trust me.

13:36.816 --> 13:38.734
And if he does?

13:38.735 --> 13:41.153
Oh, well, then,
I got something else for him

13:41.154 --> 13:42.447
he'll like a lot less.

13:45.367 --> 13:47.577
♪ ♪

13:48.662 --> 13:49.788
Oh, shit.

13:50.789 --> 13:52.665
Duffy. Duffy!

13:52.666 --> 13:55.376
<i>They're here. I'm going radio silent.</i>

13:55.377 --> 13:57.212
[panting]

13:59.339 --> 14:01.341
♪ ♪

14:12.602 --> 14:14.062
[car alarm chirps]

14:18.066 --> 14:19.066
[officer] Help you?

14:19.067 --> 14:20.359
Hey, man, how you doing?

14:20.360 --> 14:21.610
I'm all right.

14:21.611 --> 14:23.821
Hey, I'm looking for a little favor here.

14:23.822 --> 14:26.490
I got popped for a deewee a few days ago

14:26.491 --> 14:28.993
and my car is sitting here now.

14:28.994 --> 14:31.370
Listen, I know I was wrong.

14:31.371 --> 14:33.455
Drinking and driving is stupid.

14:33.456 --> 14:34.540
I could have killed someone.

14:34.541 --> 14:36.542
I did the crime, I'll do the time.

14:36.543 --> 14:41.088
But the thing is that, I was out
that night with my side piece,

14:41.089 --> 14:46.468
and she thinks she left her panties
in my fucking car.

14:46.469 --> 14:48.804
And since my license got suspended,

14:48.805 --> 14:51.141
my fiancée's coming tomorrow
to sign it out...

14:52.475 --> 14:54.977
She finds another girl's coochie-covers?

14:54.978 --> 14:56.271
I'm a dead man.

14:57.856 --> 15:01.108
So my boy brought me out here
to see if we could get

15:01.109 --> 15:04.069
the incriminating evidence
out of the picture.

15:04.070 --> 15:06.071
So, what do you say, huh?

15:06.072 --> 15:08.033
Hook a brother up? I mean...

15:09.367 --> 15:11.202
...I'll make it worth your while.

15:13.496 --> 15:14.496
Huh?

15:14.497 --> 15:17.249
Sorry, I can't let you back there.

15:17.250 --> 15:19.418
[ominous music playing]

15:19.419 --> 15:22.588
I really need to get
that shit out of my car, man.

15:22.589 --> 15:24.340
I know you could use this bread,

15:24.341 --> 15:26.634
and we both know you ain't no Boy Scout,

15:26.635 --> 15:28.969
otherwise you would have
called me already for offering a bribe.

15:28.970 --> 15:32.139
Look, man, this...
this is my second week on the job.

15:32.140 --> 15:33.724
I can't afford to get fired.

15:33.725 --> 15:36.393
You know, I'm saving up for
a down payment on a place in Gorham.

15:36.394 --> 15:38.354
I lose this job, my old lady kills me.

15:38.355 --> 15:40.398
Not looking to jam you up, but I think--

15:41.232 --> 15:44.443
What the fuck did you do that for?

15:44.444 --> 15:46.028
I already killed one cop this week.

15:46.029 --> 15:48.947
Staying with Beck was supposed
to make my life easier, not harder.

15:48.948 --> 15:50.658
[sighs]

15:50.659 --> 15:52.702
[door buzzes]

15:56.915 --> 15:58.958
[tense music playing]

16:03.296 --> 16:04.631
I'm gonna go this way.

16:16.643 --> 16:18.269
[Angel] Yo, found it!

16:20.105 --> 16:21.314
This is it, right?

16:22.440 --> 16:23.691
Yeah,

16:23.692 --> 16:26.235
that's the one that rammed the Audi.

16:26.236 --> 16:28.737
Those fuckers are toast.

16:28.738 --> 16:30.824
[camera clicking]

16:33.243 --> 16:34.661
We good to go?

16:35.745 --> 16:37.871
I didn't get much sleep.

16:37.872 --> 16:38.998
Yeah, let's roll.

16:43.878 --> 16:45.088
Hold up.

16:47.590 --> 16:49.758
That's our Audi right there.

16:49.759 --> 16:52.345
♪ ♪

16:53.430 --> 16:54.723
Yeah.

17:04.858 --> 17:06.859
You said a bodyguard blew up in here?

17:06.860 --> 17:08.987
That's what I saw.

17:10.572 --> 17:12.157
Cleaner than my fucking car.

17:15.785 --> 17:17.829
Doesn't make any sense.

17:20.749 --> 17:22.875
[Reacher] These aren't Maine plates.

17:22.876 --> 17:24.710
Delaware.

17:24.711 --> 17:26.671
This ain't even one of our fleet.

17:28.173 --> 17:29.758
Crazy.

17:30.759 --> 17:33.051
It's the same exact make and model,

17:33.052 --> 17:35.137
even all fucked up in the side.

17:35.138 --> 17:37.806
It's like that car hit this car.

17:37.807 --> 17:39.141
It's not that crazy.

17:39.142 --> 17:41.351
There's probably a couple hundred thousand
of these on the road.

17:41.352 --> 17:44.313
Beck's car's probably in
some temperature-controlled lot

17:44.314 --> 17:46.524
to preserve DNA evidence.

17:50.570 --> 17:51.737
[scoffs]

17:51.738 --> 17:54.991
Well, the Army cop should know, right?

18:02.415 --> 18:04.417
♪ ♪

18:18.306 --> 18:20.682
Wait, whoa. Where are you going?

18:20.683 --> 18:22.476
Told you already, I'm tired.

18:22.477 --> 18:24.604
[scoffs]
And you just gonna run off?

18:26.689 --> 18:28.525
Come on, man, bring it in.

18:30.109 --> 18:32.361
Come on, give it up.

18:32.362 --> 18:34.322
We did that shit tonight, man.

18:35.406 --> 18:37.908
I'm moving on up like
George fucking Jefferson,

18:37.909 --> 18:39.410
you know what I'm saying?

18:40.495 --> 18:41.996
I'm going to sleep now.

18:43.331 --> 18:45.040
You do you, bro.

18:45.041 --> 18:47.417
I still got to dump
this minivan you stole,

18:47.418 --> 18:49.920
then run those pickup's plates.

18:49.921 --> 18:53.132
And then I'm gonna get mine!

19:07.772 --> 19:09.774
[quiet, dramatic music playing]

19:17.532 --> 19:18.532
[gasps]

19:18.533 --> 19:19.616
Monsieur.

19:19.617 --> 19:21.494
What were you doing in my room?

19:22.579 --> 19:23.704
Cleaning.

19:23.705 --> 19:25.205
I just got here yesterday.

19:25.206 --> 19:27.374
Yes, well, no one's stayed
in this room in a while,

19:27.375 --> 19:29.543
and I haven't been
keeping it up like I should,

19:29.544 --> 19:31.003
so when I heard you were out,

19:31.004 --> 19:32.922
I took the opportunity to clean up more.

19:34.591 --> 19:37.092
Did Beck ask you to go through my things?

19:37.093 --> 19:38.176
'Cause I'll save you the time.

19:38.177 --> 19:40.345
I didn't steal anything
and I didn't bring anything.

19:40.346 --> 19:42.764
I noticed. No laundry.

19:42.765 --> 19:44.474
These are the only clothes I own.

19:44.475 --> 19:47.395
Well, if there's anything else you need...

19:50.440 --> 19:51.858
Just some sleep.

19:52.942 --> 19:54.736
Then I'll leave you be.

20:09.083 --> 20:10.710
[sighs]

20:12.879 --> 20:14.589
[exhales]

20:20.261 --> 20:22.137
[knock at door]

20:22.138 --> 20:23.932
Shit.

20:27.685 --> 20:28.936
What are you doing?

20:28.937 --> 20:30.437
Trying to sleep.

20:30.438 --> 20:32.397
There's work to do.

20:32.398 --> 20:34.232
Go talk to Duke.

20:34.233 --> 20:36.319
He and Paulie are in the gym.

20:39.155 --> 20:40.365
[sighs]

20:50.375 --> 20:53.836
[quiet, dramatic music playing]

21:16.859 --> 21:19.611
- [quietly] Hey, Richie.
- [gasps softly]

21:19.612 --> 21:20.988
[grunts]

21:20.989 --> 21:23.657
[pants] Is everything okay?

21:23.658 --> 21:25.743
I just want you to know...

21:27.120 --> 21:28.955
...that it won't happen again.

21:30.039 --> 21:31.373
[scoffs]

21:31.374 --> 21:33.375
Okay.

21:33.376 --> 21:35.419
Richie, listen to me.

21:35.420 --> 21:37.754
It's never happening again.

21:37.755 --> 21:39.297
It already did.

21:39.298 --> 21:41.092
If Reacher weren't there...

21:42.176 --> 21:43.176
...I'd be gone.

21:43.177 --> 21:45.637
You'd probably be getting another package
in the mail with a piece of me in it.

21:45.638 --> 21:47.807
Son, don't talk like that.

21:49.684 --> 21:52.186
Don't even think about things like that.

21:53.438 --> 21:57.358
Dad, I think about it
every time I look in the mirror.

21:58.568 --> 22:00.570
[somber music playing]

22:05.533 --> 22:06.743
[door closes]

22:07.869 --> 22:10.621
[grunting nearby]

22:18.046 --> 22:20.048
[grunting continues]

22:22.300 --> 22:24.843
[labored breathing]

22:24.844 --> 22:27.220
Heard there's work to do.

22:27.221 --> 22:29.849
- You drive a truck?
- Legally?

22:31.184 --> 22:32.726
[Duke] Let's see if it's ready.

22:32.727 --> 22:35.020
Anyone ever get any sleep around here?

22:35.021 --> 22:38.273
Yeah. When we say you can. Wait here.

22:38.274 --> 22:40.776
[labored breathing]

22:40.777 --> 22:42.653
[straining]

22:55.333 --> 22:56.709
How much you bench?

22:59.045 --> 23:00.253
Don't know.

23:00.254 --> 23:01.798
Why not?

23:02.924 --> 23:04.300
'Cause it's stupid.

23:06.010 --> 23:09.263
Come on, you versus me. Let's go.

23:10.848 --> 23:11.973
No thanks.

23:11.974 --> 23:13.642
'Cause you're a pussy.

23:13.643 --> 23:16.478
Bench press proves nothing.

23:16.479 --> 23:20.857
If you really want to know who's stronger,
Bavarian arm wrestling.

23:20.858 --> 23:22.192
Never heard of it.

23:22.193 --> 23:24.487
Get behind that preacher bench.

23:27.490 --> 23:28.990
Elbow on the pad.

23:28.991 --> 23:31.744
Put your arm out like we're gonna
arm wrestle, then make a fist.

23:40.211 --> 23:43.171
I'm gonna grab your fist
and try to pull it down to the pad

23:43.172 --> 23:45.048
while you try to stop me.

23:45.049 --> 23:46.591
Just your strength against mine.

23:46.592 --> 23:48.052
Easy.

23:49.887 --> 23:52.140
Three, two...

23:57.895 --> 23:59.187
Weaker than I thought.

23:59.188 --> 24:00.397
[grunts]

24:00.398 --> 24:02.441
[labored breathing]

24:05.862 --> 24:07.070
[groans]

24:07.071 --> 24:08.947
Sorry.

24:08.948 --> 24:10.198
Hand slipped.

24:10.199 --> 24:11.950
I'll fucking kill you.

24:11.951 --> 24:14.328
Cut the shit. Truck's ready.

24:15.121 --> 24:16.163
Truck can wait.

24:16.164 --> 24:18.707
There's work to do
and boss wants it done now.

24:18.708 --> 24:20.792
Let's go.

24:20.793 --> 24:22.627
Should put some ice on that.

24:22.628 --> 24:23.713
[drops weight]

24:33.931 --> 24:36.725
Keys are in the truck
and there's a GPS in there.

24:36.726 --> 24:40.145
It'll direct you to a location
in New London, Connecticut.

24:40.146 --> 24:41.771
They're expecting you there in six hours.

24:41.772 --> 24:43.732
That's plenty of time,
even with shit breaks.

24:43.733 --> 24:45.066
What about a coffee break?

24:45.067 --> 24:47.402
Drink coffee while you take a shit.

24:47.403 --> 24:49.529
And don't speed.
We don't want you pulled over.

24:49.530 --> 24:50.780
And don't open the back.

24:50.781 --> 24:52.657
You think you can handle that?

24:52.658 --> 24:54.242
Not a problem.

24:54.243 --> 24:56.162
[birds singing]

25:14.680 --> 25:16.056
I said no fucking peppers.

25:16.057 --> 25:17.682
- Oops.
- [phone ringing]

25:17.683 --> 25:19.809
This is bullshit. I'm hungry.

25:19.810 --> 25:21.103
[Eliot] Then eat the fucking peppers.

25:22.772 --> 25:23.980
What's going on?

25:23.981 --> 25:26.107
Beck has me driving a truck to New London.

25:26.108 --> 25:29.236
<i>We need to meet up at a rest stop
so we can see what I'm transporting.</i>

25:29.237 --> 25:31.447
- They didn't tell you?
<i>- No.</i>

25:32.823 --> 25:34.241
You could be hauling Teresa.

25:34.242 --> 25:35.283
Or drugs.

25:35.284 --> 25:38.453
Or rugs. Or drugs in rugs.

25:38.454 --> 25:41.498
Or a fox in a box with green eggs
and fucking ham.

25:41.499 --> 25:44.542
Reacher, just pick a spot
where we can tear that truck apart.

25:44.543 --> 25:47.170
Copy. But I'm on a timeline.

25:47.171 --> 25:49.005
There's a good chance
Beck's having me tracked somehow,

25:49.006 --> 25:50.674
so I only have a few minutes.

25:50.675 --> 25:52.884
Enough time to plausibly
use the bathroom and grab a coffee.

25:52.885 --> 25:54.636
All right, where are you now?

25:54.637 --> 25:58.139
<i>State Route 152, set to get
on Interstate 95 at Pittsfield.</i>

25:58.140 --> 26:00.392
We're gonna have to remove
and replace some solder on the lock.

26:00.393 --> 26:03.478
Okay, there's a rest area
just past Waterville.

26:03.479 --> 26:06.231
We'll meet you there with whatever we need
to get in and out of the truck.

26:06.232 --> 26:07.358
See you there.

26:08.442 --> 26:10.194
- Reacher?
<i>- Yeah?</i>

26:11.362 --> 26:15.073
At the impound we almost got busted,
but we pulled it off.

26:15.074 --> 26:16.366
So, good work.

26:16.367 --> 26:19.327
Easy throwing
those compliments around, Duffy.

26:19.328 --> 26:20.829
You'll pull a muscle.

26:20.830 --> 26:23.123
Wiseass. I'll see you soon.

26:23.124 --> 26:25.042
- [phone beeps]
- [line ringing]

26:28.963 --> 26:30.965
[phone ringing]

26:35.803 --> 26:37.804
- You've got Neagley.
- [Reacher] <i>It's me.</i>

26:37.805 --> 26:39.723
Tell me you're in Chicago
and we're going to a Sox game.

26:39.724 --> 26:40.974
<i>Nowhere near you.</i>

26:40.975 --> 26:42.726
But I need your help.

26:42.727 --> 26:44.811
<i>Then you've got it. What's up?</i>

26:44.812 --> 26:46.688
Can you run down the jackets
on a few names?

26:46.689 --> 26:49.524
<i>Paul Van Hoven--
not sure of the spelling--</i>

26:49.525 --> 26:51.234
<i>Chapman Duke and Angel Dole.</i>

26:51.235 --> 26:54.362
Van Hoven and Dole were Army.
Not sure of Duke.

26:54.363 --> 26:56.364
- Done.
<i>- Thanks.</i>

26:56.365 --> 26:57.907
<i>I'll check in in a day or two.</i>

26:57.908 --> 26:59.784
I'll just call you
when I have the information.

26:59.785 --> 27:01.953
I can't have this phone ringing
if I don't expect it.

27:01.954 --> 27:04.122
That's kind of how phones work.

27:04.123 --> 27:05.957
If the people around me hear it,
there could be trouble.

27:05.958 --> 27:07.710
<i>What the hell are you involved with?</i>

27:09.670 --> 27:10.754
Long story.

27:10.755 --> 27:14.216
Short version,
trouble always seems to find you.

27:15.259 --> 27:16.259
<i>You know,</i>

27:16.260 --> 27:18.261
my case load's kind of light right now.

27:18.262 --> 27:20.263
- Why don't I come help?
<i>- Not on this one.</i>

27:20.264 --> 27:23.224
I know the guy running this
and I can't have anyone else involved.

27:23.225 --> 27:25.894
I'm not just anyone else.

27:25.895 --> 27:27.687
Who are you up against, Reacher?

27:27.688 --> 27:29.899
[call disconnects]

27:46.332 --> 27:47.666
All right.

27:53.297 --> 27:54.882
What the hell's he doing?

28:01.722 --> 28:03.015
[engine turns off]

28:07.186 --> 28:09.396
What's with the hold-off?

28:09.397 --> 28:11.064
In case anyone was following by car,

28:11.065 --> 28:13.900
I counted 72 seconds
from the moment I took this exit.

28:13.901 --> 28:16.778
That's the amount of time it takes
to drive a mile at 50 miles an hour.

28:16.779 --> 28:19.364
And no one would follow visually
at a distance greater than a mile.

28:19.365 --> 28:20.824
So, no one's tailing you?

28:20.825 --> 28:22.409
Not physically.

28:22.410 --> 28:24.953
There doesn't seem to be
any kind of tracker hidden in that cab.

28:24.954 --> 28:28.581
There is this GPS
I'm supposed to be following.

28:28.582 --> 28:31.084
Beck could have someone back
at the office watching my route from afar,

28:31.085 --> 28:33.837
which makes sense considering
his operation's light on manpower.

28:33.838 --> 28:36.381
Yeah, then let's get this done.
I've got an old friend coming to help us.

28:36.382 --> 28:38.509
He should be here any minute.

28:43.973 --> 28:45.515
It's hers.

28:45.516 --> 28:47.977
I've seen her in these a hundred times.

28:58.779 --> 29:00.905
Rugs.

29:00.906 --> 29:04.452
Better than the alternative,
we could've found your girl in there.

29:09.415 --> 29:11.332
- Hey!
- Good to see you, Dickie.

29:11.333 --> 29:13.418
Can't get enough of that wonderful Duff.

29:13.419 --> 29:14.794
[chuckles softly]

29:14.795 --> 29:18.339
Reacher, Villy, this is Dick Grunert.

29:18.340 --> 29:20.925
Trains drug-sniffing dogs
for New Haven PD.

29:20.926 --> 29:23.553
We worked on a few cases together
a couple years back.

29:23.554 --> 29:26.098
Yeah, uh, and I go by Rich now.

29:27.183 --> 29:29.767
And this here is Pfizer.

29:29.768 --> 29:31.144
- Pfizer?
- Yeah.

29:31.145 --> 29:32.896
Because drugs are her business.

29:32.897 --> 29:34.397
You're a fucking idiot.

29:34.398 --> 29:37.108
Yeah, but I can train
the shit out of a canine.

29:37.109 --> 29:39.903
Pfizer! <i>Rauschgift!</i>

29:39.904 --> 29:41.321
There we go. [grunts]

29:41.322 --> 29:43.531
That's thick plastic wrap on those rugs.

29:43.532 --> 29:47.702
Well, the dogs I train can smell
a Christmas fart on New Year's.

29:47.703 --> 29:50.205
And Pfizer's the best
I've ever worked with.

29:50.206 --> 29:51.331
Just like Duff.

29:51.332 --> 29:54.459
Don't know if that's
a compliment or an insult.

29:54.460 --> 29:55.543
[Grunert] Eh.

29:55.544 --> 29:59.047
Dry as Utah on Sunday.
Sorry, Duff. [grunts]

29:59.048 --> 30:00.591
No drugs.

30:04.345 --> 30:08.181
If you're trying to prepare yourself
for what you might find, don't bother.

30:08.182 --> 30:11.685
Can't be done. Just ask the question.

30:15.022 --> 30:17.398
What if there's a cadaver in there?

30:17.399 --> 30:21.820
Well, if there was a body in there,
dead or alive, she would've found it.

30:22.863 --> 30:24.365
Thanks, Rich.

30:25.407 --> 30:27.201
Sure thing. Come on, girl.

30:28.744 --> 30:31.454
No drugs, no body to get rid of.

30:31.455 --> 30:33.748
What'd they even send you
on this trip for?

30:33.749 --> 30:36.167
[tense music playing]

30:36.168 --> 30:37.585
It's a loyalty test.

30:37.586 --> 30:39.796
Russian roulette proves I have guts.

30:39.797 --> 30:42.131
Making the delivery
proves I can be trusted.

30:42.132 --> 30:44.426
Not if we don't get moving again,
right now.

30:47.763 --> 30:49.347
Hey, we still need to solder the lock.

30:49.348 --> 30:50.723
I'll handle that.

30:50.724 --> 30:52.850
Take this GPS and start driving your car.

30:52.851 --> 30:55.436
If anyone's tracking me,
they'll think the truck's en route.

30:55.437 --> 30:58.940
Pull off at the first rest stop after the
first highway sign that reads New London.

30:58.941 --> 31:01.109
- Duffy and I will meet you there.
- Done.

31:01.110 --> 31:02.443
[sighs]

31:02.444 --> 31:04.237
You ever used one of those before?

31:04.238 --> 31:06.364
Just to get a guy to talk.

31:06.365 --> 31:07.866
[chuckles]

31:10.911 --> 31:11.953
Oh.

31:11.954 --> 31:13.162
[♪ The Beta Band: "Dry the Rain"]

31:13.163 --> 31:17.625
<i>♪ This is the definition of my life ♪</i>

31:17.626 --> 31:20.003
<i>♪ Lying in bed in the sunlight ♪</i>

31:20.004 --> 31:22.213
<i>♪ Choking on the vitamin tablet ♪</i>

31:22.214 --> 31:26.634
- <i>♪ The doctor gave
in the hope of saving me...</i>
- [phone chimes]

31:26.635 --> 31:29.762
[scoffs] You're not gonna believe this.

31:29.763 --> 31:31.306
Try me.

31:31.307 --> 31:33.975
I had a hunch about something,
so I reached out to ICE.

31:33.976 --> 31:36.019
Ever since we got onto Beck,

31:36.020 --> 31:39.606
I couldn't square up
how he's been able to stay so low profile.

31:39.607 --> 31:42.942
No flags at Customs,
no holdups in shipments.

31:42.943 --> 31:47.071
So I asked ICE for search-rate stats
from ports all over the world.

31:47.072 --> 31:48.323
That what you got on your phone?

31:48.324 --> 31:50.700
Yep. And from what I can see,

31:50.701 --> 31:53.036
Zachary Beck's shipments are searched

31:53.037 --> 31:55.204
ten times less than anyone else's.

31:55.205 --> 31:56.998
Always clean?

31:56.999 --> 31:58.625
As a fucking whistle.

31:58.626 --> 32:01.294
That search rate reads like
he's paying off someone at Customs

32:01.295 --> 32:03.129
and getting to choose
which shipments he wants searched

32:03.130 --> 32:04.297
just to keep up appearances.

32:04.298 --> 32:06.382
Mm-hmm. How it seems.

32:06.383 --> 32:08.217
- [truck horn honks]
- Easy, lead foot.

32:08.218 --> 32:11.305
We need to make up time.
We're almost to Villanueva.

32:14.016 --> 32:17.143
You know, Angel said he, Duke, all of 'em,

32:17.144 --> 32:20.355
they're not working for Beck.
He's not the one giving orders.

32:20.356 --> 32:21.899
Then who is?

32:24.401 --> 32:26.027
Quinn?

32:26.028 --> 32:27.528
Didn't ask.

32:27.529 --> 32:30.156
Can't let on I know
more than I'm supposed to.

32:30.157 --> 32:32.533
But if we're taking bets,

32:32.534 --> 32:34.911
I'd say we're getting close.

32:34.912 --> 32:37.622
<i>♪ Junkyard fool with eyes of gloom...</i>

32:37.623 --> 32:40.500
Earlier, you told me
there was no way to prepare

32:40.501 --> 32:43.253
for what I might see
if Teresa was in the truck.

32:44.713 --> 32:47.507
You said that like
you knew it from experience.

32:47.508 --> 32:49.300
[somber music playing]

32:49.301 --> 32:52.095
I worked with a kid like Teresa once.

32:52.096 --> 32:56.349
She was young,
but smart, capable, determined.

32:56.350 --> 32:58.769
A natural, like you said Teresa was.

33:00.771 --> 33:01.980
What happened?

33:03.482 --> 33:05.234
What did Quinn do to her?

33:12.866 --> 33:13.951
Okay.

33:15.661 --> 33:16.912
I get it.

33:26.755 --> 33:28.757
[dramatic music playing]

33:33.262 --> 33:36.306
[brakes squeal, hiss]

33:46.150 --> 33:48.693
Well, guess I'll see you soon.

33:48.694 --> 33:50.237
Guess so.

34:03.500 --> 34:04.917
[brakes hiss]

34:04.918 --> 34:06.627
We've been waiting.

34:06.628 --> 34:08.087
Duke said not to speed.

34:08.088 --> 34:10.215
He also said don't be late.

34:25.230 --> 34:26.315
Rugs.

34:27.900 --> 34:31.278
You work for a rug company.
What'd you think was in there?

34:32.529 --> 34:33.739
Give me the keys.

34:37.034 --> 34:39.202
Get your ass in that truck,
get back to the warehouse.

34:39.203 --> 34:41.330
[tense music playing]

34:45.667 --> 34:47.669
♪ ♪

35:01.683 --> 35:03.560
[brakes squeal, hiss]

35:07.606 --> 35:08.982
[grunts]

35:16.657 --> 35:18.659
[suspenseful music playing]

35:26.250 --> 35:27.792
[Angel] Reacher!

35:27.793 --> 35:29.044
That you, my man?

35:35.801 --> 35:37.593
Where is everyone?

35:37.594 --> 35:41.681
Got off early. Not much to do
until the next shipment's in.

35:41.682 --> 35:45.142
But I had to wait here, for you.

35:45.143 --> 35:47.563
You were tracking my route.

35:49.231 --> 35:50.524
Someone had to.

35:52.067 --> 35:53.609
Where's Duke?

35:53.610 --> 35:55.862
I thought he was gonna pick me up.

35:55.863 --> 35:57.905
On the way.

35:57.906 --> 36:00.576
But I wanted to talk to you first.

36:04.162 --> 36:05.163
About what?

36:06.456 --> 36:08.833
Um, there's, um...

36:08.834 --> 36:12.712
a few things from our trip
to the impound lot that

36:12.713 --> 36:15.299
did not sit right with me, you know?

36:16.633 --> 36:20.678
At first, I thought you were
just stalling in the gas station,

36:20.679 --> 36:22.680
couldn't figure out why.

36:22.681 --> 36:26.434
But then, you protected that cop.

36:26.435 --> 36:28.269
I knocked him out cold.

36:28.270 --> 36:29.813
Yeah, you didn't let me shoot him.

36:30.898 --> 36:31.898
Next time, then.

36:31.899 --> 36:32.983
Eh...

36:34.192 --> 36:38.322
Then I was dumping the minivan--
you know, the-the one you "hot-wire."

36:39.948 --> 36:42.408
I decided to take a closer look,

36:42.409 --> 36:46.288
and there wasn't even a scratch
on the steering column.

36:47.873 --> 36:50.666
You didn't use a screwdriver
to break into it.

36:50.667 --> 36:51.918
I used my hands.

36:51.919 --> 36:53.586
[sighs] That's impossible.

36:53.587 --> 36:56.255
I'm strong. Ask Paulie.

36:56.256 --> 37:01.802
Also, there wasn't any insulation on
the mats from stripping the wires either.

37:01.803 --> 37:03.346
I tossed it.

37:03.347 --> 37:05.306
[laughs]

37:05.307 --> 37:07.934
Okay, okay, okay. So,

37:07.935 --> 37:10.603
while you were in the process
of stealing a car,

37:10.604 --> 37:13.481
you picked up the tiny pieces
of insulation

37:13.482 --> 37:15.733
and threw them out?

37:15.734 --> 37:16.901
What the fuck for?

37:16.902 --> 37:19.278
[vehicle approaching]

37:19.279 --> 37:21.239
[horn honking]

37:22.366 --> 37:24.952
That's Duke. I need to go.

37:26.078 --> 37:28.538
There's something
I don't like about you, man.

37:29.623 --> 37:32.500
There's a lot of things I don't like
about you, so I guess you're ahead.

37:32.501 --> 37:34.086
You're dirty.

37:35.712 --> 37:40.217
I have, like, a seventh sense
for these things.

37:44.429 --> 37:45.638
You're a cop.

37:45.639 --> 37:47.556
You already knew I was an M.P.

37:47.557 --> 37:51.061
No, no, no, no, no.
I mean you're working with them.

37:52.688 --> 37:54.105
- [horn honks]
- You know what?

37:54.106 --> 37:56.440
Why don't we ask Duke

37:56.441 --> 37:58.610
what he thinks of what I just-- [grunts]

38:07.577 --> 38:08.996
[thunder rumbling]

38:11.415 --> 38:13.750
[grunting, straining]

38:19.965 --> 38:21.382
[horn honks]

38:21.383 --> 38:22.843
[grunting]

38:26.805 --> 38:28.432
[horn honking]

38:31.893 --> 38:33.019
[bone cracks]

38:33.020 --> 38:34.855
[horn honking]

38:38.900 --> 38:40.444
[honking continues]

38:55.333 --> 38:58.794
What are you, deaf? What's the holdup?

38:58.795 --> 39:00.839
Angel talks too much.

39:01.923 --> 39:03.799
[thunder rumbles]

39:03.800 --> 39:05.926
[♪ The Defiant: "Dead Language"]

39:05.927 --> 39:08.013
[singer vocalizing]

39:15.437 --> 39:19.732
<i>♪ Why go outside and leave this space? ♪</i>

39:19.733 --> 39:23.360
<i>♪ I've got the A.C. blasting my face ♪</i>

39:23.361 --> 39:26.655
<i>♪ And I'd feel awkward and out of place ♪</i>

39:26.656 --> 39:29.617
<i>♪ I've got everything I need right here ♪</i>

39:29.618 --> 39:33.329
<i>♪ At my fingertips, literally ♪</i>

39:33.330 --> 39:37.208
<i>♪ There's an app for everything ♪</i>

39:37.209 --> 39:40.503
<i>♪ So why go back to reality? ♪</i>

39:40.504 --> 39:44.381
<i>♪ It's clearly overrated, my dear ♪</i>

39:44.382 --> 39:49.553
<i>♪ Why fall in love? ♪</i>

39:49.554 --> 39:52.599
<i>♪ Love is blind ♪</i>

39:54.309 --> 39:56.977
<i>♪ Plus, who's got that kind of time? ♪</i>

39:56.978 --> 40:01.273
<i>♪ And now, we walk like zombies
in the land of the lost ♪</i>

40:01.274 --> 40:04.777
<i>♪ A pre-fabricated universe,
our eyes are all crossed ♪</i>

40:04.778 --> 40:08.280
<i>♪ Rest in peace, you dead language
and the time that you've cost ♪</i>

40:08.281 --> 40:11.117
<i>♪ Thank the Lord for opposable thumbs ♪</i>

40:11.118 --> 40:14.995
<i>♪ Asleep at the wheel,
crawling from the curb to the door ♪</i>

40:14.996 --> 40:18.374
<i>♪ I've had some deep conversations
with my living room floor ♪</i>

40:18.375 --> 40:21.877
<i>♪ I should've died at 27
like my heroes before ♪</i>

40:21.878 --> 40:25.131
<i>♪ But I was too busy having fun ♪</i>

40:25.132 --> 40:28.050
<i>♪ And now, we're too busy getting dumb ♪</i>

40:28.051 --> 40:30.137
[singer vocalizing]

40:33.265 --> 40:35.307
<i>♪ Why fall in love? ♪</i>

40:35.308 --> 40:36.893
<i>♪ I heard it's blind ♪</i>

40:37.978 --> 40:41.147
<i>♪ Plus, who's got that kind of time? ♪</i>

40:41.148 --> 40:44.441
<i>♪ And I can't dance,
and I don't drink wine ♪</i>

40:44.442 --> 40:47.237
<i>♪ So what the hell is in it for me? ♪</i>

40:48.280 --> 40:52.909
<i>♪ Why fall in love? ♪</i>
